<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7563> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7563" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Perhaps a senator (App. BC 5.49); put to death along with Cannutius after the capture of Perugia in 40. Identified by Gardthausen (Augustus 2.1.98, note 21) with C. Flavius Hemicillus (11) (see above), but he probably died at Philippi. (TJC)[91]\n" .
